						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in another grove of trees.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">A.D. 1855, Ānanda, Āṉi.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription, in corrupt language, records a gift of a flower garden and an Iluppai tree grove to provide for a lamp to the god Tirupurāntakasvāmiyār by Aṇṇāsāmimudaliyār and others, sons of Muttiyā-mudali of Vaṟāya-gōttiram of Kumarachcherivu.</p>						

